e quadrants, we can cover all 62 squares. This is possible because we can use the dominoes to cover the squares in a way that minimizes the number of dominoes used.\n\nTo summarize, we can cover the remaining 62 squares of a chessboard with two opposite corners removed by using dominoes that each cover exactly 2 adjacent squares. We need a total of 31 dominoes to cover 62 squares.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 9\nE (Epist",
